    <question>
        <prompt>John W. Davis's role in the 1924 presidential election was as:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The Republican nominee</option>
            <option letter="b">The Democratic nominee after 103 ballots</option>
            <option letter="c">A third-party candidate</option>
            <option letter="d">The vice presidential nominee</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>John W. Davis became the Democratic presidential nominee in 1924 after a bitter convention fight that required 103 ballots to reach a decision. As a compromise candidate between the party's conservative and progressive wings, he represented neither faction effectively. His campaign struggled against incumbent Calvin Coolidge, resulting in a decisive Republican victory.</explanation>
